getchar(): 
getchar()- reads a single character from the standard input (keyboard). 
In the program, ch = getchar(); reads a character and stores it in the variable ch. putchar(ch); prints the character stored in ch. 
scanf(): 
scanf() reads formatted input from the standard input. 
scanf("%d", &num); reads an integer and stores it in the variable num. 
printf("You entered: %d\n", num); prints the integer stored in num. 
gets(): 
gets() reads a string from the standard input until a newline character is encountered. gets(str); reads a string and stores it in the array str. 
puts(str); prints the string stored in str. 
/*Using Basic Data Types and I/O Operations in C programming to demonstrate Operators Data Input and Output scanf(), printf(), gets (), puts() .*/ 



